First Lady Michelle Obama, PBS, and WGBH Boston have announced the winners of the Healthy Lunchtime Challenge, a nationwide recipe challenge for kids that promotes cooking and healthy eating. The winners, representing all U.S. states, four territories, and the District of Columbia, will attend a Kids' "State Dinner" at the White House hosted by Mrs. Obama on July 10. The winning recipes were chosen based on their healthiness, affordability, originality, and taste. The challenge received almost one thousand entries featuring wholesome ingredients. The winners will join the First Lady for a healthy lunch featuring a selection of the winning recipes, followed by a visit to the White House Kitchen Garden. The full list of winners and recipes can be found online.